%p I used the above three lists to create simple questions which I then answered:

%ul
  %li Q: In MLlib, How to create an algorithm?
  %li
    A: One way to create an instance of an algorithm is to create a Transformer.
    For example I can use a type of Transformer called a Model to
    read a DataFrame of features and output a DataFrame with a column of predictions.
  
  %li Q: In MLlib, How to create a DataFrame?
  %li A: I created my first DataFrame using syntax I found at the URL listed below:
  %li
    %a(href='http://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/ml-pipeline.html#example-estimator-transformer-and-param' target='x')
      http://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/ml-pipeline.html#example-estimator-transformer-and-param
  %li
    .syntax
      %pre
        %code.scala
          val training = spark.createDataFrame(Seq(
          (1.0, Vectors.dense(0.0, 1.1, 0.1)),
          (0.0, Vectors.dense(2.0, 1.0, -1.0)),
          (0.0, Vectors.dense(2.0, 1.3, 1.0)),
          (1.0, Vectors.dense(0.0, 1.2, -0.5))
          )).toDF("label", "features")
  
